   COMPLETE entry, no itemized pass/fail, no explicit "gate met/not
   met" verdict. BuildPlan.md's merge protocol (lines ~178-183) states
   explicitly: "A merge requires proof, not a specialist's word... No
   entry, no merge — go dispatch the missing check instead of
   proceeding on trust," and this is stated to apply to every wave.
   `senior-fullstack-developer`'s own Tier 0 COMPLETE entry even flags
   this itself ("tester should still independently verify... this
   agent's own COMPLETE entries are not a substitute for that per the
   'no entry, no merge' rule") — but the commits landed on `main`
